Description: unsupervised coverage-guided kernel fuzzer
 syzkaller is an unsupervised coverage-guided kernel fuzzer.
 It supports fuzzing Linux, FreeBSD, Fuchsia, gVisor, NetBSD,
 OpenBSD, and Windows kernels. It uses KCOV-based coverage
 feedback to guide test generation and can automatically
 reproduce and bisect found bugs.
 .
 The package provides syz-manager, syz-fuzzer, syz-executor
 and related tools for kernel fuzzing.
